1. Dataset Overview 

For this CA, we decided on a public dataset of car listings. Our source for this dataset was kaggle.com (1 CSV file, 17.2 MB) with it collecting data on price, year, mileage, city, state, vehicle identification number, make and model of the cars. The dataset we analysed had 851,123 unique rows of data, making the dataset very large in size however giving us a lot of data to work with as a whole. 
 
 

2. Data Cleaning 
 
To ensure that the data was cleaned thoroughly, we removed all duplicates that was in the dataset, we did this to ensure that the metrics weren't inflated and to remove redundant data. After removing the duplicates, we proceeded to remove data with missing values (e.g. mileage or model was missing in some rows) as it may lead to inconsistent data and distort our analysis of the data itself. Finally, to finish our cleaning of the dataset, we conducted a check for any structural errors or mistakes in the format of the data, examples of this include checking for grammatical errors and making sure data is consistently in the same format.  
